WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.788
Open CRM in the left rail.

p02
00:00:02.504 --> 00:00:05.042
The sidebar stacks every kind of customer record: members, gift cards, house accounts,

p03
00:00:05.380 --> 00:00:09.089
and the four we cover today.

p04
00:00:09.772 --> 00:00:11.215
One page per record type.

p05
00:00:11.806 --> 00:00:15.593
Learn where each one lives and you stop guessing which screen holds the answer.

p06
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:17.392
Click Prepaid Books.

p07
00:00:17.896 --> 00:00:21.630
A prepaid book is a stack of washes a customer already paid for.

p08
00:00:22.201 --> 00:00:23.725
The tiles up top count them: total, active, completed, and how many expire soon.

p09
00:00:24.201 --> 00:00:27.965
In today's capture those numbers were still loading,

p10
00:00:28.699 --> 00:00:33.920
but the labels tell you exactly what to read.

p11
00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:35.608
Now the list itself.

p12
00:00:36.643 --> 00:00:39.382
Six columns, and two do the work on a call:

p13
00:00:40.053 --> 00:00:41.932
Remaining tells you washes left, Expiration tells you the deadline.

p14
00:00:42.424 --> 00:00:44.282
The rows failed to load in this capture,

p15
00:00:45.116 --> 00:00:51.765
so read the column headers and refresh live before you promise a customer anything.

p16
00:00:52.306 --> 00:00:53.685
Click Vehicles.

p17
00:00:54.176 --> 00:00:57.634
This is the master plate list, nearly four thousand cars.

p18
00:00:57.931 --> 00:00:59.093
The tiles loaded here: total vehicles, active members, flagged, and new this month.

p19
00:00:59.606 --> 00:01:07.360
When a plate gets flagged at the gate, Flagged is your first stop.

p20
00:01:07.831 --> 00:01:08.821
Scroll to the list.

p21
00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:10.862
Seven columns: plate, make and model, year, customer, location, status, last visit.

p22
00:01:11.304 --> 00:01:12.133
For a dispute you want License Plate and Status.

p23
00:01:12.451 --> 00:01:12.944
The rows hit the same fetch error, but the tiles above prove the data is there.

p24
00:01:13.484 --> 00:01:26.925
It just didn't stream into the table.

p25
00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:29.031
Click Retail Customers.

p26
00:01:29.993 --> 00:01:31.853
This one is bare on purpose.

p27
00:01:32.168 --> 00:01:36.509
No tiles, no charts, just a search box and five columns:

p28
00:01:36.932 --> 00:01:40.465
customer, plate, home location, email, phone.

p29
00:01:41.220 --> 00:01:45.464
It holds walk-ins and non-members, the people without a full membership record.

p30
00:01:46.237 --> 00:01:48.479
Search, read the contact, done.

p31
00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:49.884
Click Bundles.

p32
00:01:50.452 --> 00:01:53.076
A bundle is a packaged deal a site sells.

p33
00:01:53.368 --> 00:01:54.423
The tiles loaded: thirty-two bundles, twenty-eight active, and this month's sales and revenue.

p34
00:01:54.815 --> 00:01:59.023
The Revenue by Bundle panel ranks which packages actually move,

p35
00:01:59.606 --> 00:02:06.561
so you can see the Monthly Value Pack carrying the month.

p36
00:02:07.094 --> 00:02:07.864
Now the list, and this one actually loaded.

p37
00:02:08.121 --> 00:02:09.487
Seven columns, and five packages on screen,

p38
00:02:09.800 --> 00:02:15.592
from the Summer Special to the Fleet Pack built for fleets.

p39
00:02:16.236 --> 00:02:20.650
Watch the Valid At column: some run at every site, others only at a couple.

p40
00:02:21.121 --> 00:02:24.851
That column settles most "does this work at my location" questions.

p41
00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:27.802
One more entry, Fundraiser, sits right below Bundles.

p42
00:02:27.802 --> 00:02:29.313
Do not click it.

p43
00:02:29.313 --> 00:02:32.822
Its link goes nowhere and the page was never built.

p44
00:02:32.822 --> 00:02:36.692
It is parked, so treat the menu item as a placeholder

p45
00:02:36.692 --> 00:02:40.160
and never promise a customer a fundraiser feature from this screen.

p46
00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:42.880
So, four lists, one sidebar.

p47
00:02:43.424 --> 00:02:46.143
Prepaid Books for washes left and expiry.

p48
00:02:46.449 --> 00:02:48.147
Vehicles for plates and flags.

p49
00:02:48.367 --> 00:02:50.484
Retail Customers for walk-ins.

p50
00:02:50.846 --> 00:02:52.947
Bundles for what's on the menu and where.

p51
00:02:53.415 --> 00:02:55.008
Match the ticket to the list, open it, read the row.

p52
00:02:55.245 --> 00:02:59.200
That's the whole job on these four screens.

